# Project: Austin's Resume & Portfolio

Vite-powered, modular static site. A highly-personalized SPA-ish resume, with
AI chatbot, lazy-loaded portfolio, theme toggle, demo viewer, contact form.

## Tech stack (don't introduce new runtime deps without a strong reason)

- Build: **Vite 5** (ESM, `?raw` imports, `manualChunks`, `public/` for legacy assets)
- Runtime: plain JS (ES2018 target) + **jQuery 1.12.4** (legacy plugin bridge only)
- Testing: Node-based static checker + Puppeteer-core smoke test
- Deployment: any static host (GitHub Pages / Vercel / Netlify); `base: './'`

## The three architectural rails (do not cross)

1. **Config-first, not magic-constant-first.**
   Any new external URL, timeout, lazy threshold, secret, vendor script path,
   or feature flag MUST live in `src/config/index.js` (freeze-grouped under
   `ENDPOINTS` / `VENDORS` / `TIMINGS` / `LAZY` / `ACCESS` / `FLAGS`).
   Runtime modules should import from `src/config`, never hardcode strings.

2. **Boot through the pipeline, not through `main.js` edits.**
   Registering work at startup is done with
   `pipe.register(PHASES.X, 'label', fn)` in `src/main.js`. Do not grow the
   boot function by inlining imperative `await` chains. The five phases are:
   `PRE_MOUNT → MOUNT → POST_MOUNT → ENHANCE → DEFER`. Inside a phase tasks
   run in parallel; between phases they are sequential.

3. **Error isolation by default.**
   Tasks registered in the pipeline are wrapped by `safeRun` — a single
   module throwing MUST NOT break the others. When writing a new module,
   never `throw` from the top-level init; log via `createLogger('tag')`
   and return.

## Module layout (SRP, one concern per file)

```
src/
├── main.js            # Entry: only registers tasks into the pipeline
├── config/
│   └── index.js       # Single source of truth for constants & feature flags
├── core/              # Cross-cutting infrastructure, business-agnostic
│   ├── lifecycle.js   # Pipeline + PHASES
│   ├── safe-run.js    # Error-isolated task runner
│   ├── vendor-loader.js  # <script> injection with dedupe/retry/timeout
│   ├── lazy.js        # whenVisible() IntersectionObserver helper
│   ├── schedule.js    # rafThrottle / debounce / whenIdle
│   └── logger.js      # Level-gated tagged logger
├── modules/           # Business modules. Heavy ones may have a sub-dir
│   └── demos/         # e.g. demo-viewer's sub-concerns
└── sections/          # HTML partials (imported via Vite ?raw)
```

- `src/modules/*` depend on `src/core/*` and `src/config/*`, **never** the
  other way around. `core/` and `config/` must stay pure / reusable.
- If a module grows past ~200 lines with multiple concerns, split it (see
  `modules/demos/` as the reference pattern).
- Legacy jQuery plugins stay as raw files under `public/assets/js/` and are
  injected at runtime through `core/vendor-loader`. npm only locks
  `jquery@1.12.4` as the global bridge. **Do not port plugins to npm** —
  that's an explicit design choice to avoid behavioral regressions.

## CI gates — always keep green

- `npm test` runs both:
  - `test:static`: structural assertions (required files, `main.js` imports,
    `sections.js` canonical order, `demo-viewer` delegation, etc.)
  - `test:smoke`: Puppeteer E2E (9 sections, 6 vendors, render counts,
    privacy gate, lazy-load, theme round-trip, preloader, **0 pageerror /
    0 console.error / 0 failed same-origin requests**)
- If you add a new structural invariant, add an assertion to
  `scripts/check-structure.mjs`. If you add a new user-visible behavior,
  add an assertion to `scripts/smoke.mjs`.

## Branching, commits, PRs

- Feature branches **must** be named `cursor/<kebab-case>-a8a4` (the suffix
  is required for auto-merge routing).
- One logical change per commit; messages use conventional prefixes:
  `feat` / `fix` / `refactor` / `perf` / `build` / `docs` / `test` / `ci`.
- Open PRs as **ready for review** (not draft). The `auto-merge` workflow
  only triggers on non-draft PRs from `cursor/` branches (or those labelled
  `auto-merge`); GitHub will squash-merge automatically once CI is green.
  See `.github/workflows/auto-merge.yml` for the exact condition.
- `main` is protected — never force-push, never commit directly.

## Comments policy (matches existing code)

- Comments explain **why** / trade-offs / non-obvious intent.
- No narration comments ("// increment counter", "// import module").
- Don't explain the change you're making in the code — that belongs in the
  commit message / PR description.
